Besides being located in the historic Liberties area of Dublin 8, close to the world famous Guinness Brewery and just a stoneâ€™s throw from the city centre and main attractions like Temple Bar and Grafton Street, it provides you with a well equipped kitchen connected to a rooftop terrace overlooking the Dublin Skyline and the mountains beyond. In case of a rainy day, our TV and music room are always ready to be used!

properties.overview:
Marguerite House is a recently refurbished red brick house and is owner managed. We are located in Glasnevin is famous for amongst others, its stunning Botanical Gardens.

It is nicely decorated with a welcoming atmosphere. On arrival you will be treated to Tea or Coffee and we be happy to help you in any way.

The Botanical Gardens and Croke Park (one of the biggest stadiums in Europe) are a short walk away. We are also close to Dublin City University and the Helix Theatre.

There are many pubs and restaurants situated near by.The Sunnybank Hotel and Bar with the Phraya Thai restaurant is just across the road. Also close are chinese, indian and italian restaurants.

The Mater and Bon Secours Hospitals are also located in the surrounding area.

We are located ten minutes from the City Centre and Temple Bar area by bus or car and about 15 minutes from Dublin Airport and Dublin Port Ferry Terminal.

We have en-suite rooms with cable TV.  Double/Twin/Triple or single rooms available.

Breakfast is served between 8.30am and 10am approx. Full Irish, Vegetarian and Continential Breakfasts available.

Smoking is not permitted in the property.

Marguerite House is located on Marguerite Road which is just off Botanic Road, Glasnevin. A Bus stop is just 2 minutes away. All routes take you into the City Centre.Buses include No 4,13,19,19a and 83.  For more information, please contact us directly.

properties.overview:
What do you need to know about Jacobs Inn? We were recently ranked in the top 10 Irish hostels here on Hostelworld!

Want to know what the Lonely Planet Guide says about us? 
'This clean and modern hostel offers spacious accommodation with PRIVATE bathrooms and outstanding facilities...' - Lonely Planet Dublin City Guide

So why choose us? Jacobs Inn is a funky, comfortable hostel with a wide range of accommodation options for the individual backpacker, families and groups of all sizes. All of our guests can enjoy ensuite showers and toilets and cool bar and restaurant.

You can avail of accommodation in twin or double rooms or stay in our sigature POD beds. The pod beds designed by CoDE Hostels give you all the privacy you need in a shared dorm without losing the option to socialize with your rooms mates. The dorm rooms are among the largest and most spacious in Dublin.  Our dorms, range from four pods to twelve. All pods have underbed lockers and are coded with your own personal four-digit code - no padlocks required!

Before your busy day, enjoy our new bottomless porridge breakfast.  It is tasty, vegan, gluten-friendly and a great way to start your day.  For â‚¬6 you get as much porridge as you can eat, with premium toppings such as chia seeds, hazelnuts, dates, cranberries, pumpkin and sunflower seeds, raisins, coconut flakes and more.  All this is paired with fresh orange juice and hot coffee - bottomless as well!  If you're craving something more, we have a fantastic menu at our restaurant where you can grab a latte or a bacon roll for sit-in or take-away.  Get your day started off right!

In our bar and restaurant we offer food and drinks during your stay, a great place to fuel up for your adventures around Dublin!

Wouldn't you like to stay in the best city centre location? Of course you would...well, Jacobs Inn couldn't have a better location to explore the city. Outside is the direct bus from Dublin Airport - take the 747 bus and get here from the airport in only 25 minutes! We're also opposite Busaras, the central bus station. It's only 50m from here to Connolly train station and 20m to the LUAS, while O'Connell St is just 500m away. It's an easy walk to the O2 and Croke Park and only three DART stops to the Aviva Stadium. All tourist attractions, restaurants, bars and shops (including Trinity College and Temple Bar) are but a short stroll away.

You can chat with our friendly staff and get their advice on how best to enjoy our beautiful city. They can even sell you tickets for the best tours!

**** Please note that families travelling with children under the age of 16 are required to book private rooms. *****

- Groups of 8 or more persons will need to pay a damage deposit and sign our Code of Conduct on arrival. These groups must also pay a non-refundable deposit of 20% of the stay and pay the remaining balance 4 weeks prior to arrival. No refund will be given for group reservations cancelled within 4 weeks prior arrival..

- We have security cameras in the public areas..
